    "<p>Expert in the German Art of the Middles Ages.": [],
    "Baum studied art history at the universities of Munich, Berlin and T\u00fcbingen, where he worked under <a href=\"/vollk\">Karl Voll</a> and <a href=\"/wolfflinh\">Heinrich W\u00f6lfflin</a>.": [],
    "He completed his dissertation in T\u00fcbingen in 1905 on the churches of the architect Heinrich Schickhardt (1558-1634) under <a href=\"/langek\">Konrad von Lange</a>.": [],
    "Baum wrote his habilitation under <a href=\"/weizsackerh\">Heinrich Weizs\u00e4cker</a> in Technische Hochschule in Stuttgart.": [
